<h2>Solar Incentives in Chicago</h2>
<p>Chicago residents can take advantage of several valuable solar incentives that significantly reduce the upfront cost of installation. The federal Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost through 2032, stepping down to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. Illinois offers the Illinois Solar Renewable Energy Credits (SRECs) program, where homeowners can earn credits for every megawatt-hour of solar energy produced, typically worth \$35-\$75 per credit annually. The state's Future Energy Jobs Act also provides additional rebates through the Illinois Solar for All program for qualifying low-to-moderate income households. ComEd participates in Illinois' net metering program, allowing customers to receive credit at the retail rate for excess energy fed back into the grid. Property tax exemptions for solar installations mean the added home value from solar panels won't increase property taxes, and sales tax exemptions apply to solar equipment purchases in Cook County.</p>

<h2>Best Solar Companies in Chicago</h2>
<p>When selecting a solar installer in Chicago, prioritize companies with proper Illinois licensing, including electrical contractor licenses and solar installer certifications. Look for installers with extensive local experience who understand Chicago's specific building codes, permitting requirements, and weather challenges. Quality installers should offer comprehensive warranties covering equipment (typically 20-25 years for panels, 10-15 years for inverters) and workmanship (minimum 5-10 years). Verify the company's insurance coverage, Better Business Bureau rating, and customer reviews from other Chicago installations. Reputable installers will conduct thorough site assessments, provide detailed proposals with production estimates based on local weather data, handle all permitting and ComEd interconnection paperwork, and offer post-installation monitoring and maintenance services. Avoid door-to-door salespeople and always obtain multiple quotes from established local companies with permanent Chicago-area offices and service capabilities.</p>

